Scottish high schools continue to exhibit academic excellence, and this has continued in 2018 with an additional one-year outstanding exam results. These are supported by individual and joint success in sports, arts, music and other community activities.
These schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools, have more than 30,000 students across Scotland, and work hard to deliver the best school experience to both students and parents.
Primary schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen careers and their position as world citizens.
As an educational body that can design and implement a tailor-made curriculum, we see that modern languages are still a popular and in demand choice in schools.
Nelson Mandela once said, “If you speak to a man in a language he understands, the words come to his head.
