Scottish high school schools aim to create a learning environment that will prepare children and equip them with the knowledge and skills they need to succeed, no matter what the future brings.
It cannot be denied in today’s global business environment that language is still crucial for the country’s future, and this must be reflected in teaching.
Modern languages should in fact be regarded as “international communication ability”.
Schools will continue to offer this opportunity, diversity and award for Scottish youth.
We have to do it right.
